.TH "URL.CREATEOBJECTURL_STATIC" "3JS" "July 23, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
URL.createObjectURL_static \- URL: createObjectURL() static method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers, except for
Service Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]createObjectURL()\f[B]\f[R] static method of the
\f[CR]URL\f[R] interface creates a string containing a blob URL pointing
to the object given in the parameter.
.PP
For more information, see blob URLs.
.PP
To release an object URL, call \f[CR]revokeObjectURL()\f[R].
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is \f[I]not\f[R] available in Service
Workers due to its potential to create memory leaks.
.RE
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
URL.createObjectURL(object)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]object\f[R]
A \f[CR]Blob\f[R] (such as a \f[CR]File\f[R]) or \f[CR]MediaSource\f[R]
object to create an object URL for.
.SS Return value
A string containing an object URL that can be used to reference the
contents of the specified source \f[CR]object\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
See Using object URLs to display images.
